args: In the Halidom, Renee—the youngest of the three\nblacksmith siblings—is working as hard as ever.
I restocked all the charcoal, Ramona!
Can you give me a hand here, Renee?
I need you to put all of this\nequipment away.
I'm almost done here, Renee!\nAre you ready to cool it?
Yessss! It's Renee's time to shine!
(It's my job to cool the heated steel,\nand it's SUPER important!)
(It's pretty much the most important part\nof our whole deal! ...Um, probably.)
I need help with a couple of rather\nsimple tasks, and I thought Renee might—
Hey! My job is NOT simple, mister!
Now, now, you need to be polite to guests.\n...Understand, Renee?
Honestly, I do not get you sometimes...\nNow then, how can we help you, Malka?
I was hoping Renee could help me\nrepair some armor.
I hear you excel at providing support,\nso I expect great things from you.
I mean, I'm not THRILLED to be doing\n＂simple tasks,＂ but I can't say no when\nsomeone's asking me for help.
That's what I wanted to hear.\n...Or mostly, at any rate.
So you just want me to repair all of this\ndamaged armor? Easy-peasy!

It may not be as straightforward as
you believe. Each one is damaged in
a different place, which means you
must address them in different ways.
Huh, okay. Well, I'll give it a shot!
Okay, lemme see... Looks like fasteners\non this one are broken. This'll be a cinch.
You worked that out quickly—\nand fixed it with skill, as well.
Hee hee! My sisters have me well trained.

Looks like the belt snapped from being
under too much pressure. Maybe I'll try
to strengthen it by putting two pieces
over one another...

And nooow... Oh, this one just has a dent.
Hammering it back into shape from the
other side would reduce its durability,
but if I mix in melted steel...
Fascinating... Not only can she judge how\nto fix them, she instantly comes up with\na method of reinforcement as well.
Hey! Are you making fun of me?!
Heavens, no. I speak only the truth.
The difference between you and myself\nat your age is impossible to overstate.
You certainly are—helping your sisters\nhas clearly given you a solid foundation\nupon which to build.
Bleeech. You make it all sound\na lot less cool.
Listen to me, Renee: Experience is the\nfuel that makes artisans grow.
Indeed. The more experience you gain in\nyour youth, the more potential for growth\nyou will have as an adult.
And with your potential, you are on the\nway to becoming a first-class blacksmith!
So if I experience loads of stuff, I could\nbe an AWESOME blacksmith one day?
Precisely. And given a wide enough\nvariety of experiences, you may even\nbe one who goes down in history.
Then I gotta get going NOW!
Oh, I don't think there's such a great hurry.
You just SAID I have to do more\nthan smithing, right?
So I'm gonna go back to the castle\nand do WHATever with WHOever!
Er, that wasn't exactly what I—
Hee hee! I'm gonna be the best smith\nin the world before you know it!
Byeeee, Malka! Thanks for the tiiiip!
*sigh* I do wish she would work on\nlistening to others.
The experience I spoke of was focused\non smithing, not...random tasks.
Still, experience in itself is no bad thing;\nI hope she finds nothing but success.
Hey! She didn't finish these repairs!\n*sigh* I suppose I'll do them myself...
